org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: Territory of Washington vs. C.F. Reed etal.
United States of America Territory of Washington } ss. County of King
To H.G. Thornton and the Keeper of the Jail of Said King County

Whereas at a Justices Court held at my office in said County for the trial of C.F. Reed for the offense hereinafter stated the said C.F. Reed was convicted of having on the --- day of April 1888 in said County committed the crime of obtaining money under false pretenses and upon conviction the said court did adjudge and determine that said C.F. Reed should give a bond with two sufficient sureties in the sum of $250 and stand committed until the cause be paid and whereas the said C.F. Reed has made default in the payment of the cause - Therefore you the said H.G. Thornton are hereby commanded in the name of the United States forthwith to convey and deliver the said C.F. Reed to the said Keeper and you the said Keeper are hereby commanded to receive the said C.F. Reed into your custody in said jail and him there keep until he shall thence be discharged by due course of law. Dated this 23 day of April 1888
N. Soderberg Justice of the Peace
